SUPPORT for Pravin Gordhan is growing.Gerhard Papenfus, CEO of The National Employers Association of South Africa, has thrown his weight behind Gordhan.In an open letter of support to Gordhan yesterday, Papenfus said: It seldom happens that within the context of a country so much depends on one man. South Africa finds itself at such a point in its history and you, Minister, are that man. He said over 15 000 businesses and individuals had expressed support for Gordhan in just a few days. On the weekend, 81 CEOs also pledged their support for Gordhan. ANC members such as Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa and the party s chief whip, Jackson Mthembu, have also declared their support for the minister. FIN24